282
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:22,700
Roger.

283
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,490
I'm home.

284
00:20:27,030 --> 00:20:30,700
Ohh, John. Good boy.

285
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:38,500
Takanori, how's it going,

286
00:20:39,630 --> 00:20:41,340
with your studies for college acceptance?

287
00:20:41,340 --> 00:20:42,260
Not very well.

288
00:20:44,010 --> 00:20:46,100
Are you home today?

289
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:51,390
About your daughter, she's been coming home late.

290
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:55,770
She's only 18. Will you say something to her?

291
00:20:55,770 --> 00:20:57,900
Isn't that your job?

292
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:03,030
Stocks.

293
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:04,030
Daddy?

294
00:21:04,530 --> 00:21:10,200
What color was the sea, when you went to the south on your business trip?

295
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,250
Color of the sea?

296
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:13,000
I don't know.

297
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:16,380
Daddy was busy with work.

298
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,090
No one may believe me, but...

299
00:21:21,710 --> 00:21:25,380
...I became a pirate in the South Seas.

300
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:29,100
That huge ship was today's prey.

301
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:31,890
Let's get back to port before lunch.

302
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:34,390
The China bowl at Tao Han...

303
00:21:36,020 --> 00:21:38,020
...sells out fast.

304
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,130
We're being targeted by pirates?!

305
00:23:23,130 --> 00:23:25,300
What's the background on our client?
